title: Yes

input.atr: is an eia designated as a public document and made accessible to the public before permitting the development?  how is the eia accessed?

name: Yes
description: EIA legislation is a public document by law

properties.evidence: Cha 4-29 Documents related to env clearence shall be kept on record at the office of the secatariet or CA and made available to the public upon request

Chapter 4: article 29 Documents related to environmental clearance shall be kept on record at the Office of the secatariate or the CA and made available to the public on request.                  Ch4-28 When the decision on the Env clearance has been taken the secatariet or the CA shall make a public announcement of the decision and make the following info available: the discription of the project  - the Env terms - mitigative measures -main reasons and considerations on which the decision is based including the basis for the acceptance or rejection of veiws and arguments presented by other authorities, and concerned people   a non technical summery
11-1 The ministry shall communicate the Env decision statement to the proponant and make it available on the Ministry's Website

Article 7 The federal agency shall maintain separate Registers for IEE and EIA projects which shall contain the particulars of each project and a summery of the decision taken, and which shall be open to inspection by the public at all reasonable hours and the disclosure of this infomation in such registers shall be subject to the restrictions mentioned before
Art. 20(2)(a) requires, as part of the law's public debate requirements, that the EIA report be made available for 1 month to the general public and environmental non-profits.

Art. 25(6) mandates that the ministry place an electronic copy of the Profound EIA Report, the Non-Technical Summary of the EIA and the additional information provided by the developer on its website. Moreover, Art. 26(2), requires the developer to notify the public in local and national newspapers that a Profound EIA Report has been submitted to the Minsitry and is available for inspection both at the developer's office and on the Ministry's website.  Copies of the EIA report are available for a "reasonable"fee =MEDIUM Level of public access

Art. 9(3)no.3 The authority shall announce place and time of possible inspection.  9(3)no.4 Authority shall also announce the project on the Internet and attach a brief description of the project and a non-technical summary of the environmental impact statement.

Article 8(1)  The heads of the affected community, within 5 days of receiving the EIA report inform the public through mass media where and when it is possible to familiarize oneself with the documents and obtain data (oral or written).

Article 10(2) Within 7 working days of issuing the statement, the relevant authority shall send the
statement to the notifier, affected administrative authorities and affected territorial self-governing
units. Within the same period of time, it shall publish the statement on the Internet and shall
ensure that it is made available to the public pursuant to article16.

Article 10(2) Within 7 working days of issuing the statement, the relevant authority shall send the
statement to the notifier, affected administrative authorities and affected territorial self-governing
units. Within the same period of time, it shall publish the statement on the Internet and shall
ensure that it is made available to the public pursuant to article16.
The Authority shall make public announcement of the final approval The EIA report has to be publicly accessible.

15. Access to environmental information
(1) Persons or agencies holding environmental information 
concerning the likely environmental impact of an activity or the 
status of the environment at a site shall make such information available without charge to the developer, decision-maker, expert and person exercising supervision.The documentation in EIA proceedings is easily accessible because there is legal obligation to publish the EIA programme (results of the scoping phase) and the EIA report in the Internet.
The EIA report must also be published electronically and sent to the appropriate authorities for their information.

Access to the entire EIA documentation is ensured by the competent environmental authority within five working days of its availability. the clerks of the the potentially affected municipalities must publish the EIA decision within five days by posting in public places and in in ways according to local custom.

Availability of the copies of
EIA documents as well as other
documents is regulated by the Law
on the Rights to Receive Information
from Municipal and State Institutions
of the Republic of
Lithuania.
When state environmental review is made one copy of the decision is submitted to the regional environmental authorities for information and for the purpose of supervision in future.
The EIA and related documents are designated as public documents. Presumably available at any time during the process. Art 18: "All citizens have a right to the information regarding the EIA"
